HEADWORD: Rubescent
<hw>Ru*bes"cent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>rubescens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>rubescere</ets>
to grow red, v. incho from <ets>rubere</ets> to be red: cf. F.
<ets>rubescent</ets>. See <er>Ruby</er>.]</ety> <def>Growing or becoming
